
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `nisdomainname` baraye namayesh ya ta’een name domain NIS (Network Information Service) estefade mishavad. Agar bedune gozine-ha ejra shavad, name domain NIS فعلی ra chap میکonad. Agar ba yek name domain ejra shavad, name domain NIS ra ta’een میکonad (نیازمند دسترسی مدیر (root) hastید).

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 No gozine khas. Dastoor aslan gozine-ha nadarad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ nisdomainname

    🔹 Namayesh name domain NIS فعلی.

    $ sudo nisdomainname example.com

    🔹 Ta’een name domain NIS be "example.com" (نیازمند دسترسی مدیر).

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ nisdomainname
    example.net
    $

    🔹 Dastoor name domain NIS ra chap میکonad. Dar inja, "example.net" name domain NIS ast.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `nisdomainname` command is used to display or set the NIS (Network Information Service) domain name.  When run without arguments, it prints the current NIS domain name. When run with a domain name argument, it sets the NIS domain name (requires root privileges).

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 No specific options. The command does not accept options.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ nisdomainname

    🔹 Displays the current NIS domain name.

    $ sudo nisdomainname example.com

    🔹 Sets the NIS domain name to "example.com" (requires root privileges).

✅ **Simple Example & Explanation:**

    $ nisdomainname
    example.net
    $

    🔹 The command prints the NIS domain name. In this case, "example.net" is the NIS domain name.

